# Start here / Org controller & docs

When the user says **"use org-controller"** or **"use docs"**:

1. **Call the org-controller MCP server.** Use the **`org_getting_started`** tool first — it returns the bulk of org preferences and getting-started context.
2. **Apply what it returns.** Follow any coding standards, conventions, branch names, and preferences from that response for the rest of the conversation.
3. **Use other org-controller tools as needed.** The org-controller MCP server has additional tools; use them when relevant (e.g. docs, preferences).

Do not suggest or use `main` as the default branch; the user prefers **`master`**.
